Merge pull request #314 from asterics/Deinhofer/ARE-Webserver-https feat(Deinhofer/are webserver https):
* a https webserver and REST interface to prevent mixed content problem (fixes #266 )

The following ports are used
8081: http webserver + REST interface (no SSL)
8082: websocket (ws://)
8083: https webserver + REST interface (SSL with self-signed certificate)
8084: websocket SSL (wss://): not working yet.

also added simple websocket client, to easier test socket connections
Merge branch 'fix-ARE-window-resolution-and-fonts'

As we use Java 8, the screen size and resolution handling is not done in a good way, with Java 9 this should be better: http://openjdk.java.net/jeps/263 On Windows the toolkit size is smaller than the primary screen size, if the desktop is scaled up (e.g. 125% or 150%). On Linux the toolkit size seems to be the whole virtual screen size when having multiple monitors, on windows not. --> if the toolkit screen size is smaller than the primary one, use the smaller one.

Refactored and modularized code for the REST and websocket initialization and starting. The following ports are used 8081: http webserver + REST interface (no SSL) 8082: websocket (ws://) 8083: https webserver + REST interface (SSL with self-signed certificate) 8084: websocket SSL (wss://): not working yet. also added simple websocket client, to easier test socket connections

Per default ports 8081-8083 are activated, the secure websocket does not work yet, so it was disabled.
TODO:
 * Maybe use CA-signed certificate for not having to add an exception when connecting to the ARE https URL on Firefox

Added support for 2 REST server and 2 Websocket channels  * The first pair is http (8081), ws (8082)  * The second pair is https (8086) and wss (8087). But the secure websocket (wss) does not work yet. The ports can be configured in bin/ARE/areProperties
Will also add flag to disable the functionalities.

Merge pull request #313 from asterics/fix-ARE-window-resolution-and-fonts fix(Fix ARE window size and font rendering):
* the ARE window size and location calculation on multi display environments (especially on Linux, where Toolkit.DefaultToolkit.getScreenSize() returns the virtual screen size).
* Make use of the method AstericsGUI.getScreenDimension on all occasions.
* Max font size calculation for the TextDisplay and EditBox plugins
* introduces a method ```AstericsGUI.calcMaxFontSize()``` to have a centralized method that can be used by any plugin.
* enables anti-aliased font rendering for cellboard cell text.
* also added AstericsGUI.getMaxFontSize method, which overrides max font size to 10 in case of a low screen resolution (w < 1440 || h < 900). This **fixes #243**

added method AstericsGUI.getMaxFontSize():  * This method returns the maximum allowed font size to use for all ARE GUI elements. The maximum font size is dependent on the configured size in areProperties ({@link AstericsGUI#DEFAULT_FONT_SIZE_PROPERTY}) and overridden in case of a low screen resolution.

added setting of properties to ensure rendering of Antialiased fonts added rendering hints for CellBoard cells to also use Antialiasing for the text rendering. --> The CellBoard cells are not that ugly any more :-) See: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/2d/text/renderinghints.html
https://batsov.com/articles/2010/02/26/enable-aa-in-swing/

added method AstericsGUI.public float calcMaxFontSize(JComponent component, Dimension widgetDim, String testString)  * calculates the max font size for the given component, it's preferredWdigetDim and a given testString. The calculation of the max fontsize was buggy (only widgetHeight but not widgetWidth was considered). Furthermore, we can ensure a systemwide equal font size now

use AREServices.instance.getScreenDimension (AstericsGUI.getScreenDimension) instead of Tookit.getDefaultToolkit... to ensure that the size calculation works in the same way (screen size of primary display) for elements and plugins. fixed bug with constant value of  AppId Variable (http://www.jrsoftware.org/ishelp/index.php?topic=setup_appid) when using the InnoSetup installer creation (.exe)  For a problem description, see: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/33482340/java-fx-applications-installing-in-same-directory/44545147#44545147

 The id attribute of the fx:application tag is used to create the AppId variable in .iss files. Before we used the constant value "fxApplication" for it.
 Now we use the value of the property ${fx.application.name}

fixed gui updates of TextArea plugin: The instantiation, deletion and updates of the TextArea gui were not done within SwingUtilities.invokeLater. So it was likely to meet a race condition especially at slow computers or in a virtual machine. We must use invokeLater and not invokeAndWait because invokeAndWait blocks and could thus lead to a dead lock.

Fixes #100: Activated usage of findjava.bat to find the best JRE (32-bit) which is installed on the system

Improved #100: In some cases the JRE is not registered in the registry, so added additional search strategies. In total there are 7 now: 1) in case this is an installed AsTeRICS with an embedded java in the java subfolder
2) otherwise, first search for the current 32bit jre installed in the registry
3) otherwise, search for the current 32bit jdk having an embedded jre installed in the registry
4) next, try the programdata symbolic link
5) next, search for an entry in the %ProgramFiles(x86)% subfolder, because this is the normal location for java 32-bit installations
6) if we could not find anything else, search in the 64-bit  standard installation folder
7) Try if %JAVA_EXE% is in path, because this could be any other than the standard paths in theory.

The strategies are tried in the given order. As soon as one is successful the java.exe is checked for the correct version (>=1.7) and the full path is returned

Improved ResourceRegistry.getResource: The resourcePath now supports windows and unix-style paths and characters. A resourcePath can be  an absolute URL-conforming string (e.g. file://, http://). In this case the string must be encoded correctly.  or an absolute or relative file path (windows or unix-style). In this case {@link File} class and its method {@link File#toURI()} is used. The file path may contain both \\ and / seperators. Relative resourcePaths are resolved against the ARE.baseURI or a subfolder depending on the provided type ({@link RES_TYPE}). Merge pull request #82 from asterics/singleThreadedStabilization Single threaded stabilization

Merge pull request #81 from asterics/singleThreadedStabilization A lot of optimizations to for the single threaded approach:

If a call in the ModelExecutor thread takes to much time a TimeoutException is thrown and the 'hanging' thread is exchanged with a new thread.

To prevent very fast and enormous amounts of tasks a bounded queue of size 500 is used that rejectes new tasks if the queue is full.

@see class AstericsModelExecutionThreadPool for details

added flag pluginReady to indicate if plugin has been initialized completely and is ready for processing coordinates. Actually this should not be necessary because the plugin is executed in one single thread but the facetracker native code obviously has a timing problem if the callback thread already sends coordinates while loadCameraProfile or setDisplayPosition is called.
consequently set mouseActive flag in start/stop/pause/resume to ensure that no callbacks can interfere

commented also out mainFrame.validate
and icon.revalidate invocations

because it seems that those interfere with the mouse robot if there are still some queued robot tasks

Set DEFAULT_EXECUTOR_QUEUE_SIZE to 500 to not reject too many tasks if the computer is slow. TODO: make this parameter configurable in areProperties and also check if execute could be optimized to not always queuue

removed all synchronized keywords, because the model will be executed in single threaded mode. Actually it should not be a problem but just to be sure that a hanging model executor does not hold the lock and thus prevent the fallback model executor from entering the synchronized code block. GUICell: repaintNow uses invokeLater instead of invokeAndWait just to be sure that no dead lock situation could arise.
In case of deployModel and deployFile do the execution of stopModel before the try block, to not fall into the catch block

readded the synchronized(stack) and synchronized(row) statements again to still work in case of multi-threaded approach. But note: The multi-threaded approach is deprecated and will be disabled in a future release.

The model executor now uses a ThreadPoolExecutor with a bounded queue of size DEFAULT_EXECUTOR_QUEUE_SIZE. If the queue is full a new task is rejected. This is done to prevent that the ARE is knowcked down in case of a hanging task due to a thread dead lock or a blocking I/O call. Also ensure that the method execAndWaitOnModelExecutorLifecycleThread always will get the chance to execute, also if the queue is full.

Fixes #14: A single-threaded approach is now used for the execution of a model. This way concurrent modification of plugin data is impossible In case of a hanging model (due to hanging I/O call,...) a fallback thread is used to still be able to stop a hanging model. This way the ARE keeps sane and can still be used to execute other models afterwards.

Three properties were introduced (Can be configured in areProperties):
#Determines size of model executor thread pool. If 0 or 1, the single-threaded approach is used. If > 1 the multi-threaded approach is used with a pool of the given size.
ThreadPool.ModelExecutor.size=0
#The size of the thread pool for other tasks like CIM communication. This pool is used by many plugin to perform some "parallel" tasks
ThreadPool.OtherTasks.size=10
#Maximum time in milliseconds to wait until a blocked execution in the model executor thread is timed out.
ThreadPoolTasks.submitTimeout=7000

Fixes #48: Now any to any data type of the schema definition is implicitely converted. These are: byte char string integer double boolean The conversion is done following the rules of casting in Java
e.g. in case of doubleToInteger the upper bytes are skipped, the same for the decimal part
special case boolean:
a string value "true" --> true
a string value of any number and the number != 0 --> true
a string value of any number and the number == 0 --> FALSE_BITS
any other string --> false
